<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-08-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="33" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d33">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">FW 841.51/8–1247</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the British Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Balfour</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-08-14">August 14,
                                        1947</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Chargé d’Affaires</hi>: I have
                                received your letter of August 12<note n="1" xml:id="d33fn1">Not
                                    printed.</note> advising me that your government’s delegation
                                for the forthcoming talks on financial matters will arrive in
                                Washington this weekend in anticipation of discussions beginning
                                Monday.</p>
                            <pb facs="0074" n="56" xml:id="pg_56"/>
                            <p>On our side these discussions will be conducted by the National
                                Advisory Council on International Monetary and Financial Problems,
                                of which, as you know, the Secretary of Treasury is Chairman. I have
                                informed Mr. Snyder of the contents of your letter.</p>
                            <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert</hi> A. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>